\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf0 OVERVIEW\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 This project provides a powerful, highly customizable background driver for the Elgato Stream Deck on macOS. It replaces the official software, offering deep integration with shell commands, AppleScript, and a configuration workflow based entirely in Apple Numbers.\
It is managed via a local web UI and is designed for power users who want to control their Mac's command-line tools with the press of a button.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 KEY FEATURES\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'95 
\f0\b Apple Numbers Configuration:
\f1\b0  Configure all your buttons in a user-friendly Streamdeck sheet in Apple Numbers.\
\'95 
\f0\b Web-Based Management:
\f1\b0  A lightweight, local web UI (http://localhost:8765) allows you to view your button layouts and variables in real-time.\
\'95 
\f0\b Powerful Flag System:
\f1\b0  Augment buttons with simple flags to enable advanced features like device targeting, connection monitoring, background processes, and more.\
\'95 
\f0\b Variable Support:
\f1\b0  Embed dynamic variables like \{\{TAKE\}\} or \{\{IP_ADDRESS\}\} directly into your commands. Edit them on the fly with a long-press.\
\'95 
\f0\b Automated Installer:
\f1\b0  A simple, user-friendly .dmg installer handles all dependencies and background service setup.\
\'95 
\f0\b Launchd Service:
\f1\b0  The driver runs as a persistent background service that starts automatically on login and restarts itself if it ever crashes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

