\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 CONFIGURATION: FEATURE FLAGS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Use these flags in the "Feature Flags" column (Column C) in Numbers to control button behavior.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 @ (Device Target):
\f1\b0  Marks a button as a "target device." Other buttons send commands to this device's terminal.\

\f0\b ~ (Monitor Connection):
\f1\b0  Continuously monitors an @ device's SSH connection, showing "CONNECTED" or "BROKEN".\

\f0\b * (Record Button):
\f1\b0  A stateful button. Short-press starts/stops the command. Long-press edits variables (SCENE, RECPATH).\

\f0\b ? (Keyword Monitor):
\f1\b0  Runs a command and monitors its terminal output for the "Monitoring Keyword" from Column D.\

\f0\b # (Numeric Adjust):
\f1\b0  Long-press to enter a mode where \uc0\u9650  and \u9660  keys adjust a numeric variable in the command.\

\f0\b V (Variable Edit):
\f1\b0  Allows you to edit any \{\{variable\}\} in the command with a long-press.\

\f0\b T (Sticky/Top):
\f1\b0  Pins the button to the top of the Stream Deck screen, regardless of pagination.\

\f0\b N (New Window):
\f1\b0  Forces the command to always execute in a new terminal window.\

\f0\b K (Keep Local):
\f1\b0  Forces a command to run locally, even if an @ device is active.\

\f0\b M (Mobile SSH):
\f1\b0  Transforms an SSH command (e.g., ssh root@host) for a mobile context by changing the user to mobile@.\

\f0\b & (Background Toggle):
\f1\b0  Runs the command as a silent background process. Press again to terminate it.\

\f0\b > (Confirm Action):
\f1\b0  Displays a confirmation dialog before running the command.\

\f0\b 1-99 (Font Size):
\f1\b0  Sets the label's font size. This is just the number (e.g., 22). Colors are separate flags. The default size is 13.\

\f0\b D (Dim Color):
\f1\b0  Dims the selected base color (e.g., GD for dim green).\

\f0\b R, G, B, O, Y, P, S, F, W, L (Colors):
\f1\b0  Sets the button's background color.\uc0\u8232 (Red, Green, Blue, Orange, Yellow, Purple, Silver, Fuchsia, White, Light)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
